In response to the message sent  Wed, 13 Aug 86 12:05:12 MST from llp@arizona.edu

The RNAME field in the SOA is supposed to be a person you can complain
to if the zone has problems.  For example, if you think that TTLs are
absurdly low, a delegation doesn't help with glue address RRs when
required, etc.  This field was put in the SOA to guarantee its presence,
and most domains have a reasonable value.

Some have suggested additional information such as phone numbers, or
contact points for all hosts, operator phone numbers, etc... but
for domains I think we are already have what you want.

paul
